alert.note: Alert for Monmouth; Ocean (New Jersey) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly (New Jersey, Delaware, Southeastern Pennsylvania)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 29 at 9:43AM EDT by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM EDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues. * WHERE...Portions of central and southern New Jersey...including the following counties...Monmouth and Ocean. * WHEN...Until 400 PM EDT Saturday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 935 AM EDT, Excessive rainfall overnight and this morning has resulted in water on roadways and high water in streams and creeks. Excessive water continues along shore areas especially near Barnegat Bay. This will continue as the high tide arrives later this afternoon. - Some locations that may experience flooding include... Toms River, Long Branch, Asbury Park, Lakewood, Middletown, Howell, Marlboro, Barnegat, Tinton Falls, Holmdel, Red Bank, and Beachwood. - This includes the following highways... Interstate 195 in New Jersey between mile markers 25 and 34. Garden State Parkway between mile markers 57 and 118. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around...don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Do not drive around barricades or drive through water of unknown depth.
